snippet.textDisplay:
Hate to disappoint all of you modern day "supercar" fanboys and fangirls out there, but the "supercars" which were produced by companies such as Motion Performance back in 1968/1969/1970 era were putting out better ET numbers in the 1/4-mile right off of the "showroom floor", and on bias-ply tires (no slicks) and a whole lot less hi-tech (and at a cheaper price, adjusted for the time period, I might add). Also, these ETs were achievable with manually shifted transmissions as well.

Other than the driver, tire technology has always been and will continue to be the limiting factor in transferring all of that engine power/torque to the ground efficiently, especially in a drag race. Thems da' facts...😄👍🇺🇸
